    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A former Postal Service employee was indicted yesterday in the fatal shooting of two postal workers and two customers during the $5,000 robbery of a Montclair post office in March. If convicted on four of the five counts of the indictment, Christopher Green, 29, of East Orange, could face the Federal death penalty.</p>
        <p>Faith S. Hochberg, the United States Attorney who will be trying the case, said that Mr. Green knew the slain postal workers and "executed" them so they could not identify him.</p>
      </block>
